<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="559" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1015,1256]" pageId="8" pageNumber="559">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1015,1040]" pageId="8" pageNumber="559">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be recognized by presenting following features: fourth palpal segment without long setae. Male genitalia with gonostyle slender and long; parameres fused, into single plate; aedeagus broad with rounded apex. Female with one seminal capsule (
<bibRefCitation author="Szadziewski" box="[703,1041,1087,1112]" pageId="8" pageNumber="559" refString="Szadziewski, R. &amp; Havelka, P. (1984) A review of the Palaearctic biting midges of the subgenus Brachypogon (s. str.) (Diptera, Ceratopogonidae). Polish Journal of Entomology, 54, 341 - 358." type="journal article" year="1984">Szadziewski &amp; Havelka 1984</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
